review_text: Pesen latte ternyata pake cup plastik murah pdhl harganya diatas j*nji ji*a. Rainbow slide mahal, 20k/1x meluncur. Yg paling bikin sebel bbrp hr lalu kesana lg & PELAYANAN SUPER LELET. 1,5 jam yg dtg cuma makanan & minum blm, pdhl cust yg dtg setelah sy semua pesanannya sdh ada. Berkali2 minta dipercepat tp zonk, akhirnya dtg ke kasir minta dibikin saat itu jg sambil di tungguin. Itupun salah pesanan, pesan 1 ice tea yg dtg 3 & masuk ke bill jd terpaksa dibayar. Mungkin kekurangan karyawan krn wkt itu ada gathering, yg melayani gathering + pengunjung biasa pelayan nya itu2 aja. Tp no excuse ya, yg namanya buka usaha hrs punya manajemen waktu yg baik. Soalnya emg dr awal buka s/d sekarang, kopi gincu ini pelayanannya lelet bahkan saat sepi pengunjung. Owner & management nya tolonglah berbenah
review_translated_text: Ordering a latte turned out to be in a cheap plastic cup even though the price was above promise. Rainbow slide is expensive, 20k/1x slide. The most annoying thing is that I went there again a few days ago & THE SERVICE WAS SUPER SLOW. After 1.5 hours, only food and drink arrived, even though the customer who arrived after me had all the orders. I asked several times to speed it up but I was stuck, finally I came to the cashier and asked to make it right then and there while waiting. Even then the order was wrong, ordered 1 ice tea which came 3 & was added to the bill so I had to pay. Maybe there was a shortage of employees because at that time there was a gathering, those who served the gathering + the usual waiters were the only ones. But no excuse, opening a business requires good time management. The problem is that from when it first opened until now, this gincu coffee service has been slow even when there are few visitors. Owner & management, please improve

review_text: Padahal kopi gincu ini udah punya nama, cuma dari pelayanan kurang mulai dari meja yang lama dibersihinnya, kemudian komunikasi antar pelayan masih sangat kurang, keramahan dan profesionalitas dari pelayan juga kurang. Saya harap pelayan2 di kopi gincu lebih diperhatikan lagi kualitas dan profesionalitasnya terutama dalam kesigapannya. Saya datang ke sini saat kondisi caffee sedang ramai tetapi kesigapannya sangat kurang dan banyak terjadi miskomunikasi. Saya harap pemilik kafe juga bisa memperhatikan kembali terkait penggunaan teknologi yg bisa mempermudah komunikasi antara pelanggan dan pelayan agar tidak terjadi kembali Miss komunikasi seperti ini. Untuk tempatnya sendiri kopi gincu ini sudah tergolong strategis dan lumayan nyaman, tetapi pelayanannya masih sangat amat kurang bagus.
review_translated_text: Even though this gincu coffee already has a name, the service is just lacking - starting from the tables taking a long time to clean, then the communication between the waiters is still very lacking, the friendliness and professionalism of the waiters are also lacking. I hope the waiters at Gincu Coffee pay more attention to their quality and professionalism, especially their alertness. I came here when the cafe was busy but the alertness was very poor and there was a lot of miscommunication. I hope that cafe owners can also pay attention to the use of technology that can facilitate communication between customers and waiters so that communication errors like this dont happen again. As for the place itself, this gincu coffee is considered strategic and quite comfortable, but the service is still very, very poor.

review_translated_text: A very bad experience from a very unfriendly way of serving from time to time. The 5 of us waited for more than an hour even though the crowds were quiet when the first drink was delivered which was okay and safe. Then the waiter brought crushed fried rice and said You ordered nasgor, didnt you? then I said yes so how come we, the one who delivered it, said we didnt order it than I answered in fact, weve been waiting for food that never came. I came, indeed I saw the waiter bringing the nasgor for the next table so the waiter said oh well this is the nasgor sis in my heart said OMG half the nasgor was ruined but never mind, well it was just the nasgor that came and there were still 2 dishes who didnt arrive until more than an hour later, we came at 9 until it was almost closing at 10, then one of us went to the kitchen and took his order and what happened was that the waiters were playing on their cellphones, God forbid, after one of you came back and said something like Then the last food that we had been waiting for came and the waiter gave it with a sullen face and just put it on the side of the table and immediately left, instantly breaking our mood. review_translated_text: I love the ambience, suitable for me time, doing office work or writing a thesis even on weekends but its not too busy here. Since Covid, Ive been here again. But this time it was a bit confusing because the barista wasnt focused enough :) Firstly, I explained what size I wanted but he seemed confused and confused even though he had already said it clearly twice, secondly he offered me a split bill (Sbux card balance + cash) so I just said yes because Its good that I have a balance of 50 thousand and Im too lazy to open banking. After that, he told me to scan it and then I just scanned it, but I dont know why it didnt reduce the balance and I still paid in full using cash, hahaha, thirdly, I asked for the caramel latte to be made later, when it was ready. I wanted to take it out because I wanted to take it home, I was afraid the ice would melt and it wouldnt taste good, and the barista agreed to make it together with Green Tea, so it didnt take long, 40 minutes to pull it out straight away, but I asked for less ice, but I was given a lot of ice. Hopefully next time when I come here there wont be cases like this again, hm

review_text: Minggu, 18 Juni 2023 Pas masuk outletnya, langsung disambut dengan wangi kopi yang kental. Meski bukan penikmat kopi yaa udah. Tapi tetep bisa pesen minuman lain dong. Biasanya pesen Boba Susu Gula Aren. Yummy, enak bangetlah ini rasanya. Susunya pas, gulanya pas, dan bobanya empuk lembut. Ada juga roti2an yg isinya bervarian plus menu ayam. Ak juga lumayan suka ayam bumbunya. Tapi emang kalo kesini lebih sering beli minumannya. Hehehe Harganya standart minuman yaaa 27k ukuran large, itu udah dipotong 5k karena ak udah jadi member, xixixi Kalo pake debit card BTN bisa diskon 50% looh denhan maksimal potongan 55k. Jadi kalo beli senilai 110k, cuma bayar 55k aja. Worth it banget kan. Dan ini berlaku sampai akhir juli atau agustus 2023 gitu. Enjoy it. Pelayanan petugasnya juga ramah yaaa, welcome banget. Tempatnya lumayan nyaman yg dibawah. Kalo yg diatas aku kurang tau, ga pernah ke atas soalnya. Hehehe Oke, see u on my another review ^_^
review_translated_text: Sunday, June 18 2023 When you entered the outlet, you were immediately greeted with the strong aroma of coffee. Even if youre not a coffee drinker, thats fine. But you can still order other drinks. Usually order Palm Sugar Milk Boba. Yummy, this tastes really good. The milk is just right, the sugar is just right, and the boba is soft and tender. There are also rotis with various fillings plus a chicken menu. I also quite like the spiced chicken. But I do come here more often to buy drinks. Hehehe The price for a standard drink is 27k for a large size, 5k has been deducted because Im already a member, xixixi If you use a BTN debit card, you can get a 50% discount with a maximum discount of 55k. So if you buy 110k, you only pay 55k. Its really worth it, right? And this is valid until the end of July or August 2023. Enjoy it. The staff service is also friendly, really welcoming. The place is quite comfortable downstairs. I dont know about the above, Ive never gone to the top. Hehehe OK, see you on my other review ^_^

review_text: Alfamart yang berada di jalan pertigaan ke lakbok dan banjarsari mangunjaya ini cukup terlihat jelas dan strategis. Bangunan yang cukup luas, barang-barangnya cukup lengkap tapi masih ada rak yang masih belum terisi apa emang barangnya kosong. Pelayanan ramah dan agak ngantri soalnya untuk pembayaran listrik dsb cukup memakan waktu. Parkiran cukup luas bagi motor dan mobil tapi sebaiknya tukang parkir tidak perlu ada soalnya lalu lintas kendaraan di jalan pun gk terlalu ramai.
review_translated_text: Alfamart, which is located at the T-junction road to Lakbok and Banjarsari Mangunjaya, is quite clearly visible and strategic. The building is quite spacious, the goods are quite complete but there are still shelves that are still not filled or whether the goods are empty. Friendly service and a bit of a queue because paying for electricity etc. is quite time consuming. The parking lot is large enough for motorbikes and cars, but its best not to have a parking attendant because the traffic on the road isnt too busy.

review_text: Terletak di pertigaan jalan, letaknya strategis sehingga mudah dijangkau. Barang-barangnya banyak yang kosong. Pelayanan ramah tetapi agak lambat dan menimbulkan antrian. Cemilan makanan yang kami pesan kentang goreng dan roti bakar, kentang gorengnya enak menurut saya (sudah ada bumbunya).
review_translated_text: The cafe is in a shophouse near the side of the road, so its easy to find, and the map points match. Parking is adequate for those with motorbikes and cars, so theres no need to worry. Seating is available inside (in front of the bartender and on the 2nd floor, there is also seating outside for those who want to smoke. The coffee served was not bad, we happened to order palm sugar milk coffee, Americano coffee but forgot to ask the bartender what his signature drink was. The snacks we ordered were French fries and toast, the French fries were delicious in my opinion (already had seasoning).

Stick mozzanya ini sorry ya zonk karena isinya bukan keju tapi kroket kentang yang saya gak suka. Chicken steaknya kata suami enak. Cafe anak pelajar, harganya murah dan rasanya so so. Tapi asli deh itu ice milonya enak banget, sempet balik lagi buat order take away ice milo ini.
review_translated_text: It seems like this is one of the busiest cafes in Banjarsari because the place is spacious. Its quite difficult to get good iced coffee in Banjarsari. Order the palm sugar coffee, if its creamier, its definitely delicious. This milo ice chocolate is really delicious, it tastes like milo and is thick. The mozza sticks are sorry, zonk, because they dont contain cheese but potato croquettes, which I dont like. My husband said the chicken steak was delicious. Student cafe, the prices are cheap and the taste is so so. But the truth is, the ice milo is really delicious, Im going back again to order take away ice milo.

review_text: Datang ke sini sama teman2 sekitar jam 5 sore. Pesan minuman dan makanan. Minumannya sih datangny cepat, tapi makannya datang sekitar jam 7.30 malam. Gilaaa sih. Padahal kita hanya pesan mi goreng, dan situasi gak terlalu rame dan pelayannya banyak. Bahkan mungkin lebih banyak dari pengunjung. Kecewa skali, karena kita udah bergantian datang ingatin ke karywannya..malah ada bebrapa karyawannya yg malah duduk di meja pelanggan sambil main hp dan ketawa2 aja. Dan keliatan yg di dapur hanya sibuk goreng kentang gak jelas. Karyawannya kebanyakan anak2 muda yg gak paham bagaimana cara melayani costumer dgn benar dan manajemen penerimaan pesanan yg kacau balau membuat makanan jadi tersendat. Kecewa bgt. Gak lagi ke sini deh. Tobat. Pelayannya harus diberi pelatihan lagi.
review_translated_text: Came here with friends around 5 pm. Order drinks and food. The drinks came quickly, but the food came around 7.30pm. Thats crazy. Even though we only ordered fried noodles, the situation wasnt too busy and there were lots of waiters. Maybe even more than visitors. Very disappointed, because we took turns coming to remind the employees...in fact there were several employees who sat at the customers table playing on their cellphones and just laughing. And it looks like the people in the kitchen are just busy frying potatoes, its not clear. The employees are mostly young people who dont understand how to serve customers properly and the management of receiving orders is chaotic, making food stagnant. Very disappointed. I dont come here anymore. Repentance. The waiters need to be given more training.

review_text: Salah satu tempat untuk menikmati kopi dan nongkrong di Banjarsari. Meski tempatnya tidak terlalu luas tapi memiliki rooftop dan outdoor yang memiliki panggung untuk live music. Mushola dan WC tersedia disini, namun untuk lahan parkir sendiri agak sempit sehingga cukup untuk motor, kemudian untuk kebersihan meja dan kursi yang berada di rooftop harus diperhatikan juga. Bagi penikmat kopi disini tersedia beragam menu kopi salah satu kesukaan saya adalah menu Japanese yang ditambah dengan lemon. Jadi ajak temanmu buat nongkrong disini Parking: Bayar parkir 2 ribu rupiah
review_translated_text: One of the places to enjoy coffee and hang out in Banjarsari. Even though the place is not very large, it has a rooftop and outdoor area which has a stage for live music. Prayer rooms and toilets are available here, but the parking area itself is quite narrow so there is enough for motorbikes, then you also have to pay attention to the cleanliness of the tables and chairs on the rooftop. For coffee lovers, there are various coffee menus available here, one of my favorites is the Japanese menu with lemon added. So invite your friends to hang out here Parking: Pay for parking 2 thousand rupiah

review_text: Warga Cileungsi mana suaranya?? Aku nemu coffee shop lucu nih di Cileungsi, buat yang ga tau Cileungsi pokoknya Cibubur lurus dikit lah Letaknya agak masuk ke dalem gang dikit nih, gang SMA 1 Cileungsi alias Nepal. Tapi ga terlalu masuk ke dalem jadi mobil masih aman masuk kok. Konsepnya industrial dengan area outdoor yang paling luas. Indoornya hanya untuk bar dan slowbar aja. Space areanya cukup luas bagiku jadi bisa book buat acara juga disini. Untuk menu juga lengkap. Salah satu alasan aku mampir kesini, karena liat line upnya rame dan sering ganti. Selain manual brew juga ada espresso based lainnya. Yang non kopi pun ga ketinggalan. Kalau makanan juga lengkap, ada snack dan makanan berat juga. Aku coba beberapa menu, enak semua dan harganya masih affordable.
review_translated_text: Where are the people of Cileungsi?? I found this cute coffee shop in Cileungsi, for those who dont know Cileungsi, basically Cibubur is a bit straight It is located a little bit deep into an alley, the alley of SMA 1 Cileungsi aka Nepal. But it doesnt go too deep so the car is still safe to enter. The concept is industrial with the largest outdoor area. The indoor area is only for the bar and slowbar. The space area is quite large for me so I can book for events here too. The menu is also complete. One of the reasons I stopped by here was because the line up was busy and changed frequently. Apart from manual brew, there are also other espresso based brews. Even non-coffee people are not left behind. If the food is also complete, there are snacks and heavy meals too. I tried several menus, they were all delicious and the prices were still affordable.

review_translated_text: The foods and drinks are affordable. My fav one is Rice Bowl Beef Sambal Matah The sambal matah is not spicy, its delicious. For the size of a rice bowl, the portion is quite large. The coffee is delicious, I like the mochachino. Not sweet. This place is so underrated, maybe cus the place doesnt have a good view outside     its less hyped. But, the place is comfortable, really a cafe. The parking lot is also good. Id say this cafe is a  hidden gem  because it is located protruding and cant be seen from the main road But, the plus is that its not too noisy with the sound of vehicles. If it can be improved, maybe you can consider making a smoke-free room/making certain regulations for customers who smoke. I saw some children were there and at another table there were many adults smoking. In fact, thats the room in the interior Overall 8/10, 4 times Ive been there, the taste of the food is consistent. My biggest concern is cigarette smoke. Its annoying.

review_translated_text: GET RID OF LAZY PARKING TEENAGERS, every time a trader is crowded with parking attendants, is it really the parking attendant who owns the street? Later, the parking attendants will be quiet when its their turn to sell, and they dont want to be responsible for their presence. Iced tea is indeed cheap, IDR 2,500 BUT paying for parking is IDR 2,000, its more expensive to pay for parking, you just have to push and get the money. Parking attendants dont think about recipes, supplying ice cubes, sugar, water, stoves, renting stalls, paying employees but their profits are bigger than those selling iced tea. IF YOU BUY HERE, ITS BETTER TO JUST PAY FOR PARKING SO THEY KNOW THAT ITS HARD TO GET MONEY, ITS NOT JUST PUSHING CAPITAL.
